
GIT WORKFLOW !!

Three Areas of GIT -> 

> Working Directory 
-- Where we make changes to our files. 
   Files here will be new, modified, or deleted. But, it won't save the changes until we stage and commit them.
> Staging Area 
-- Where we prepare changes before committing. 
> Repository 
-- Where our committed history is stored.
> Pushing Changes 
-- We can use this to send our commits to a remote repository like Github, so others can see them.
   [ git push ]

[working directory] -- git add --> [staging area] --git commit --> [Repository] 

